This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the problem of zero-shot learning in image classification. It also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a probabilistic approach to solve the problem. Additionally, it uses semantic attributes or text descriptions to learn from side information, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with image and text data. Finally, it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it proposes a new approach to solve a challenging problem in machine learning.
